quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  50,16,"And indeed We have created man, and We know what his ownself whispers to him. And We are nearer to him than his jugular vein (by Our Knowledge)."
  50,17,"(Remember) that the two receivers (recording angels) receive (each human being),{1} one sitting on the right and one on the left (to note his or her actions).{2}",footnotes:1:[ A (50:17) Narrated ‘Âishah رضي الله عنها The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم said: The deeds of the following three persons are not recorded by the pen:
  50,18,"Not a word does he (or she) utter but there is a watcher by him ready (to record it).{1}",footnotes:1:(V.18) See the footnote (A) of (V.6:61).
  51,10,"Cursed be the liars"
  51,11,"Who are under a cover of heedlessness (think not about the gravity of the Hereafter),"
  51,12,"They ask: "
  52,1,"By the Tûr (Mount)"
  52,2,"And by a Book Inscribed"
  52,3,"In parchment unrolled."